summary: SummaryHighlightsCruelty FreeVeganImpeccable Foundation delivers medium to full, long-lasting coverage with a natural, velvet-matte finish. Using Precision Blur Technology, it blurs pores and imperfections while Hyaluronic Acid hydrates and smooths the skin. Get seamless, flawless coverage that wears comfortably for up to 12 hours.

reviews.headline: Not good for mature skin
reviews.comments: I am 54 years old with combo (dry side) skin, forehead wrinkles and little rosacea bumps on my cheeks. The foundation blurred my pores, but my wrinkles and bumps more pronounced. It did cover the redness and minor dark spots with ease. Very quick drying.

reviews.headline: Great
reviews.comments: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] The shade range is amazing equal for everyone of different shades. The texture and coverage is my favorite part it's so blurring and hydrating it last such a long time and it's so blendable without creasing.

reviews.headline: full coverage foundation
reviews.comments: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] I was sent the wrong shade so I couldn't try it :( I'm sure it has great coverage and it's best for oily and normal skin. I can see it becoming heavy so build it lightly.

reviews.headline: Amazing
reviews.comments: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] This foundation is very smooth has great coverage and the packaging is so fancy I love it. The pump is also great, lets out good amount of product.

reviews.headline: A must have
reviews.comments: This foundation is really amazing. It blurs your pores really well and it is very full coverage. It blends very smoothly and the shade matches perfectly. Highly recommend

reviews.comments: This foundation is pretty good. Its the first one I've used in a long time, but I've been pleased with it so far. I did have to switch up the primer and setting powder I was using which is why I took one star off.

reviews.headline: Lightweight & matte?!
reviews.comments: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] Matte is finally making a come back and I'm living for it! I love a good sweat-proof formula and this is it! I love the velvet finish texture. The shade I got was very dark, but covers and is smudge-proof.

reviews.headline: Winner!! ü•á
reviews.comments: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] This foundation is a winner! It has a beautiful, natural finish that lasts all day, with a lightweight texture that blends effortlessly into the skin. There's no strong scent, which I appreciate, and the sleek packaging feels high-end. The coverage is buildable, giving me a flawless look without feeling heavy.

reviews.headline: My favourite foundation üòç
reviews.comments:
Lightweight, velvet-matte, and feels like second skin. It blurs imperfections beautifully, lasts all day, and doesn't dry out the skin-thanks to the hyaluronic acid. It applies like a filter and looks naturally flawless.
+ Impressed by its lasting power and seamless finish.
Definitely a product I'll keep reaching for.

reviews.headline: Get this!!
reviews.comments: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] Literally in love with how perfectly this matches my skin. I got this in shade 3N and normally I suck at picking / matching my foundation online. BUT WOW. This one is perfect. It blends in so seamlessly and it makes my skin look so flawless. I was literally in shock when I put this on.

reviews.headline: Thee must have foundation
reviews.comments:
[I received this product in exchange for my honest review] 
I fell in absolute love with Anastasia Beverly Hills impeccable blurring second skin foundation. I love everything about this foundation, it's literally pretty much perfect in every way. other than one pretty significant detail..the shade I ordered it in, is a few shades too dark at 1.5N. For reference, I have very fair skin dark hair, green eyes. My skin usually burns, never tans. The shade was way too dark for my skin but I love it so much I found a way to wear it. I mixed it with a lighter shade of the same foundation. This foundation is a dream come true. It's velvet like texture and the softness so buttery smooth, leaving skin looking supple and plump, covers all imperfections, all dark spots, blemishes, dark scars.. etc. It doesn't melt off, even during the hottest most miserable of days. But the biggest plus of all, is it doesn't make me break out! It doesn't clog pores. I removed it with ease, using a makeup wipe and then I washed my face as usual. It's a little on the expensive side but worth every single cent. Your face will thank you, spend a little more to have a quality foundation that won't break you out and the bottle is full of product. Especially when a little goes a long way. Make sure unlike me, you don't accidentally choose the wrong shade. Learn from my mistake please! Take all the time you need to, try on a few different shades and undertones, until you find the perfect shade for your skin. I still plan on replacing this shade with the correct shade  very soon. I give this an A+ rating, that's with the shade being way too dark. That should tell you just how amazing this is. Try it yourself & believe.

I only use a thin layer and it covers pretty well the imperfection spots. I may have to purchase another shade to match my skin though üòÖ

reviews.comments: The only reason I gave this 2 stars is because it's a thick full coverage foundation, it just doesn't last. Foundation becomes blotchy after an hour or so. I've experimented with primers, and without and the foundation just does not stay put.

faceoff_positive.comments: This is the first time trying ABH foundation. And probably would have overlooked it due to so many choices if it wasn't send to me to try it. Boy, I'm glad they did! Thanks ABH, I fell in love with this foundation. I have a combo. I usually prefer using BB or CC creams as oppose to foundations. They look much more seamless than foundations especially full coverage (light coverage foundations often just do't cover enough or don't even out skin tone in my experience). This ABH foundation absolutely blew me away and I am now rethinking my preferences. It has a very nice glass packaging that feels and looks good. A little bit goes a loooooong way. I was very surprised! I use my fingers to apply it. It has absolutely zero scent or odor to it, no funny chemical smelling business. It applies so smooth, so easy and fast. It covered all the problem areas, I didn't even need a concealer,  it even under my eyes! It looked like second skin, I could hardly tell I was wearing foundation, yet everything was covered and polished. It was also a perfect foundation for bronzer and blush. It made them look so good, so much better than it normally does. I absolutely loved it. When the foundation settles after applying, it looks matte but somehow leaves just enough glow to make my skin look healthy. My skin really did look impecable just like the name suggests. I normally skip primers, for one it's an extra step requiring extra time, two, I don't see much difference when I do and don't wear them. This ABH foundation wears really well without it. It lasted me all day. One of the days I have an allergy attack, kept sneezing and touching my nose and guess what?! The foundation, while obviously rubbed off my nose, did not look odd around my nose, everything was still very even. So, I have to say that it doesn't just breaks down on your skin with patches like many do, it wears off very nicely even on oily areas. I really have zero complaints about it. They were not exaggerating when making this one "impecable". It is really is.  Absolutely love it!
faceoff_positive.headline: Impeccable indeed! Love love love!

faceoff_negative.comments:
[I received this product in exchange for my honest review] 

This foundation sounds like my dream. But on me, it contradicts itself. For me to benefit from its skincare properties or its smoothing and blurring effects, it needs to go directly on my skin, not over a primer. It promises hydration, plumping, and a "second-skin feel".

PROMISES & CONTRADICTIONS 
 
But can it deliver on those promises on its own? Not in my experience. If I don't use a primer, even on clean, otherwise nicely prepped skin, this foundation cannot lay down nicely on my textured skin. I've tried multiple application methods - brush, sponge, fingers. Patting it on has worked best. It needs a primer, though. It dries down SO FAST when you apply it, no matter what way. It is very, very light and very matte. You have to work quickly. It sets in moments.

However, after a few hours in Texas, it completely breaks up and shows my redness and texture, now looking even rougher mixed in with broken down foundation. It highlights the very things I wanted to hide. This is supposed to last 12 HOURS!

This foundation sounded too good to be true for me, and it was. If you have redness and or textured skin, this foundation may not work for you. It is difficult to benefit from many of the capabilities it touts. 

PACKAGING & ACCESSIBILITY 

Let's talk about packaging, too. I also review products from an accessibility point of view. I have severe juvenile rheumatoid arthritis in my hands so packaging matters a LOT. I do really like the rectangle container. It is large and easy to hold and get the lid off. (Round shapes are not as easy for me.) The pump is small, however, so that is not as easy to use. (A large pump surface is much more accessible.) So that is another thing to keep in mind.  

Also, the gold cap and pump component are easily smudged and dirtied, as I depict in my pictures. I have to clean it off after every use. I also show my arthritic hands holding the product. 

All told, unfortunately I will not be switching to this as my foundation. I do think if you have smooth skin, and skill, you will do pretty nicely with it though.

I received this product to try in exchange for an honest review.
faceoff_negative.headline: You Need Smooth Skin & Skill. Somewhat Arthritis Friendly.
